1
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:26,360
"Saeng Karun Foundation"

2
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:58,920
Rise and shine, everyone.
The birds are already out.

3
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:02,080
Get up.
Or Grandpa's coming to scold you.

4
00:01:22,840 --> 00:01:25,480
Make a fist and spin it round

5
00:01:25,510 --> 00:01:27,980
Raise your hands
and wave them side to side

6
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:32,680
Spread your arms up and down,
fold and touch your shoulders

7
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:35,000
Spread your arms up and down

8
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,440
Stand up straight
and spin around

9
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:40,120
Line up.

10
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,520
Phi Oui, get me the eggs.

11
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:18,070
(Phi, respectful honorific)

12
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,000
Here.

13
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,120
Now the zucchini, Phi Oui.

14
00:02:49,820 --> 00:02:52,320
Put it down, Mom.
Leave it to the young.

15
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,680
Very well. You carry it over.

16
00:02:54,860 --> 00:02:57,120
Then come back and help Auntie Oui
lift the rice pot.

17
00:02:57,270 --> 00:02:58,440
Okay. Don't have to tell me.

18
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,080
Hmph.

19
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:02,560
- Hot stuff coming.
- Should I stop feeding you?

20
00:03:19,610 --> 00:03:21,040
Okay. Come on in.

21
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:25,260
Here. Grab it. Okay.

22
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,070
- Easy now.
- Yes.

23
00:03:27,090 --> 00:03:28,480
There we go. Okay.

24
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:31,500
You're welcome. Here you go.

25
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,200
- Alright, okay.
- Thank you.

26
00:03:34,330 --> 00:03:36,080
Give them plenty now.

27
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:37,400
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

28
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:42,680
Hey... hey, your pants.
Suck it in a little.

29
00:03:42,820 --> 00:03:43,820
There you go.

30
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,700
Hmph...watch out
or they'll fall right off you.

31
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,560
Nice job.

32
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:52,640
Stop, stop. Pik, hold on.

33
00:03:54,770 --> 00:03:57,680
Here. Do not eat boogers, okay?

34
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,720
Hey, not yet.

35
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:05,080
Phi Pipe, leave me alone.

36
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:07,330
Pipe, don't pick on her.

37
00:04:07,490 --> 00:04:09,160
Yes, Phi Save.

38
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,080
Grandpa, go sit down.

39
00:04:17,420 --> 00:04:19,270
You could pass out
blowing that whistle.

40
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,560
Stop before you drop.

41
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:21,960
It's you who will drop.

42
00:04:21,960 --> 00:04:24,560
See? With this.

43
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,160
Go on.

44
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,480
Stay with Mom, okay?

45
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,600
Yeah.

46
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:33,670
- One, two, three, four...
- Five, six, seven, eight.

47
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:38,120
- One, two, three, four...
- Five, six, seven, eight.

48
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:39,720
One...

49
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:41,380
Hehe.

50
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,960
Breakfast is ready. Stop playing.

51
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:48,480
Just a little warm-up, Grandpa.

52
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:50,510
So I can eat more.

53
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:53,600
Trying this move.
It's way more fun.

54
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:56,590
People need to do things
one at a time.

55
00:04:57,290 --> 00:04:59,030
Take your seat.
We're about to eat.

56
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:01,960
Kids these days always talk back.

57
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,200
Go on.

58
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,020
Mart.

59
00:05:13,770 --> 00:05:15,240
Any rice left?

60
00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:16,520
What's going on, Sorn?

61
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,480
Someone dropped off a kid, Dad.

62
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:20,440
She looks hungry.

63
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,120
Thank you.

64
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:18,920
Listen for the signal.

65
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:21,780
Alright, let's eat.

66
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:22,820
Yay.

67
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:42,720
- Okay, hop on in. Careful now.
- Hurry, hurry.

68
00:06:45,260 --> 00:06:46,280
Serves you right.

69
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:49,600
- Pipe.
- Pipe, at it again?

70
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:54,320
Snow, hold it. Let him go.

71
00:06:58,650 --> 00:07:00,280
Dad, let's go.

72
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,240
Okay.

73
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:04,960
Bye-bye, Grandpa.

74
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,080
- Bye-bye.
- Buh-bye.

75
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:12,320
- Oh...
- That was fast.

76
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,480
I already spoke
with the child's mother.

77
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,280
Just three lanes down from here.

78
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:29,280
No husband.

79
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,760
Just lost her job.
She really can't manage.

80
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:45,600
Girl, this place...
is your new home now.

81
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:48,680
You'll have food to eat,
a place to sleep.

82
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,400
Someone to look after you.

83
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,840
You're safe now. Okay?

84
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:55,600
Mm-hmm. Mart.

85
00:07:56,630 --> 00:07:58,630
Take her to see
where she'll be sleeping.

86
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:06,720
Great. I'll show you.

87
00:08:14,890 --> 00:08:18,640
Dad, we can't take in
any more children.

88
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:21,120
Why not? What's wrong?

89
00:08:30,930 --> 00:08:32,400
Hello.

90
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:36,280
Good morning, Supaporn
calling from Thanarak Bank.

91
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:39,080
May I speak
with Mr. Somsak Prasitphithaya?

92
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,640
Speaking.

93
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,880
The reason for my call today

94
00:08:42,910 --> 00:08:45,440
is that we have not received
a loan payment

95
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:51,160
for December 2025
through January 2026.

96
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:54,200
When would you be able
to make a payment, sir?

97
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:56,900
Very soon.

98
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:13,680
I'm dealing with
a few things right now.

99
00:09:13,830 --> 00:09:16,040
I must inform you of another matter.

100
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,660
In February 2026,

101
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:22,010
your reduced-rate agreement is
nearing the end of its grace period,

102
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:25,460
after which your payments
will resume at the standard rate.

103
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:28,680
And if I still can't pay?

104
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:33,240
We encourage you to come in
for a consultation.

105
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:36,520
Accounts over 180 days past due

106
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:40,280
will be subject to legal action.

107
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,200
I'm sorry... legal action?

108
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:45,120
What happens then?

109
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,260
Well...

110
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,270
the Enforcement Department may

111
00:09:48,270 --> 00:09:50,160
seize the land used as collateral

112
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:52,480
and sell it at auction
to settle the debt.

113
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:00,480
How much do I still owe?

114
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:02,320
Principal and interest

115
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:07,180
comes to 12,508,649.75 baht.

116
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:09,880
I see.

117
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:25,440
Was that the bank?
What did they say?

118
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:29,240
Hmm?
Nothing to worry yourself over.

119
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:35,360
Over not making
loan payments on time?

120
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:40,880
Dad, we barely can afford groceries
for the children.

121
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,720
And then there's tuition
and everything else.

122
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:46,200
Tonight they're delivering
rice and cooking gas,

123
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:48,770
and I'm afraid
I have no money for those.

124
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:52,760
It's all right. I'll sort it out.

125
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,600
There's always a way.

126
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:02,680
My elderly allowance just came in.
I'll transfer it over.

127
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:05,680
How much is it?

128
00:11:05,780 --> 00:11:06,780
Seven hundred baht.

129
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:19,360
Hey, Mom. Sitting out here again.

130
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,480
Now listen.
I've told you many times,

131
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:29,020
do not bring that out here.

132
00:11:29,290 --> 00:11:31,760
You could drop it.
Worth a lot, you know?

133
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:34,600
Come on. Give it to me.

134
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:38,160
Mm. It's getting hot out here.

135
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,640
Better go sit inside. Come on.

136
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:44,200
Come, come. Grab the cane.

137
00:11:44,610 --> 00:11:47,480
There we go. Up, up.
Can you make it?

138
00:11:47,830 --> 00:11:49,680
Alright, let's go.

139
00:11:49,990 --> 00:11:53,330
Easy steps. Go on. Go on.

140
00:11:56,650 --> 00:11:59,480
Alright, turn, turn.

141
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,440
Now, back up.

142
00:12:02,650 --> 00:12:04,820
Back up. Easy, easy. There we go.

143
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:08,600
Good. Very good.

144
00:12:20,570 --> 00:12:21,570
Huh.

145
00:12:21,930 --> 00:12:24,800
Mom, I'm heading up to work now.

146
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:13,530
"Thailand Writers' Association,
Certificate, Somsak Prasitpittaya"

147
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:26,590
"Saming the Slayer, Volume 2"

148
00:13:32,330 --> 00:13:35,120
"Saming the Slayer 2,
by Harn Chanprai"

149
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:48,420
Hmph.

150
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:52,510
Go, go.

151
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,080
Hey, hey. Watch it.

152
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:09,700
Hey.

153
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:12,100
Pheem. Pheem.

154
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:14,000
Hey, block it. Block.

155
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:17,440
- Yeah...
- Yeah...

156
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,200
- Yeah.
- What the.

157
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,720
Hey, hey. Why aren't you in class?

158
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:25,880
Get to class. Now.

159
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:32,240
Tuck in your shirt too.

160
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:34,520
You...

161
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,440
Hey.

162
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:38,520
Supawit.

163
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,090
You're on a scholarship.

164
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:44,120
Why not show your friends how to be
studious and not skip class?

165
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,600
Go before they pull
your scholarship.

166
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:50,320
Too late for that, teacher.
It's my last semester.

167
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,640
And I already got into uni.
So why must I go to class?

168
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:56,000
If you're at school,
you go to class.

169
00:14:56,510 --> 00:14:58,860
And this is no time
for soccer, right?

170
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:02,160
Besides, you two

171
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:04,640
still have final exams
just like everyone else.

172
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:09,200
Please, just this one period.
Cut us some slack.

173
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:12,040
Even if I go,
I won't pay attention anyway.

174
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:13,520
I'll just bother everyone.

175
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:15,280
You two wear me out.

176
00:15:15,590 --> 00:15:19,510
Fine. But no soccer.
The other kids can see you.

177
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:21,160
Hang out somewhere else.

178
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:23,440
- Yes.
- Got it.

179
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:24,440
Okay.

180
00:15:25,850 --> 00:15:27,240
Hey, all of you go to class.

181
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:30,080
Lucky for us,
Kru (teacher) Met came.

182
00:15:30,410 --> 00:15:32,680
Kru Suri could've dragged us
to her office.

183
00:15:32,870 --> 00:15:35,160
Well, let's bounce
before she gets here.

184
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:36,640
Yeah?

185
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,000
Ugh.

186
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:43,800
You think you got me?

187
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:25,680
Hey Guy, all your posts are
in Close Friends, huh?

188
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:27,600
Who else is in there?

189
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,600
Just you.

190
00:16:31,730 --> 00:16:32,730
And some others.

191
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,840
Who?

192
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:39,800
Secret?

193
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:41,230
No.

194
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,300
Hmm?

195
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:44,270
Not telling me?

196
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,160
Will we still be friends
after we graduate?

197
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:50,880
Why?

198
00:16:50,930 --> 00:16:54,720
Well...we'll be at different unis.
So far apart.

199
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:56,280
We won't see each other much.

200
00:16:59,570 --> 00:17:00,640
Come on.

201
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:04,220
You'll make new friends in no time
and forget all about me.

202
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:09,240
An athlete like you,
I bet you'll have a girl in a week.

203
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,720
Hey, Save.

204
00:17:19,390 --> 00:17:20,390
Yeah?

205
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,440
I just want to tell you...

206
00:17:25,370 --> 00:17:26,370
Hmm?

207
00:17:28,080 --> 00:17:29,320
Tell me what? Just say it.

208
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:34,640
We'll still be friends.

209
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:37,750
I'll make sure we hang out
all the time. Okay?

210
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:42,280
Of course. What's gotten into you?

211
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:44,450
Stuttering and spacing out.

212
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:47,190
I didn't want to
say something cheesy.

213
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:51,880
Go ahead and say it. I won't gag.

214
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:56,160
What's wrong with you?
You're being weird.

215
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:07,350
Mm.

216
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,140
- Phi Sorn.
- Hmm?

217
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,440
Is this ride far from here?

218
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:14,840
Not at all. Just two lanes over.

219
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,000
Good.

220
00:18:16,100 --> 00:18:19,290
Don't take another job yet.
I have a new project.

221
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:20,960
What project?

222
00:18:20,990 --> 00:18:23,360
Mm. Just finish the job and return.

223
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,500
Mm-hmm.

224
00:18:33,050 --> 00:18:34,050
Be careful.

225
00:18:42,460 --> 00:18:46,000
Phi Sorn, shouldn't we get
a handyman for this?

226
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:49,800
We've got everything we need.
Why waste money?

227
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:52,240
You actually know what you're doing?

228
00:18:53,230 --> 00:18:54,430
Trust me.

229
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:59,200
Just need to check the drill first.
Been sitting a while.

230
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:00,920
It may be rusted.

231
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:02,980
Here.

232
00:19:05,970 --> 00:19:08,680
Take this. Wait right here.

233
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:26,760
Oh, Grandma.

234
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:29,280
Just watching us work?

235
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,760
You just sit and watch;
no need to help.

236
00:19:31,890 --> 00:19:34,720
- We've got this.
- Oh no, Grandma.

237
00:19:34,970 --> 00:19:38,260
Just cheer us on from here.
That's plenty.

238
00:19:39,170 --> 00:19:43,450
And why are you holding that clock?
It's worth a lot, you know?

239
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:17,320
Ugh.

240
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:26,320
- Easy now.
- Good.

241
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:30,160
What are you two doing?

242
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:31,900
What is it, Dad?

243
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:36,080
Ugh.

244
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,920
Watch the hand. Be careful.

245
00:20:47,950 --> 00:20:49,570
Yeah, I know what I'm doing.

246
00:20:50,360 --> 00:20:51,840
You sure about that?

247
00:20:51,870 --> 00:20:52,960
Absolutely.

248
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:04,640
Hey, anybody kicked the plug?

249
00:21:04,870 --> 00:21:05,870
I did.

250
00:21:06,090 --> 00:21:07,090
Oof.

251
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:11,160
What's all the racket?
It drove me mad upstairs.

252
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:16,200
Phi Sorn is making a trellis
for the vegetable garden.

253
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:18,440
A trellis? What for?

254
00:21:18,670 --> 00:21:19,920
Well, it's obvious.

255
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:23,240
So we can save money on buying them.

256
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:25,980
Oh? Is that so?

257
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:26,770
Mm-hmm.

258
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,120
You all know how to do that?

259
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,760
Can't be that hard.

260
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:33,280
Drop some seeds, water them,
wait for them to grow.

261
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:35,120
Then pick and eat. Simple as that.

262
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:36,660
Mm.

263
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:40,440
Alright. Just keep it down a little.

264
00:21:40,990 --> 00:21:42,400
It's bothering me.

265
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:43,680
Yes.

266
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:52,800
Sorry, Father.

267
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:57,320
We should hurry.

268
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:03,920
Oh, Mom. Not again.

269
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:09,480
What is it with you and that clock?

270
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:12,840
Give me that.

271
00:22:21,990 --> 00:22:22,990
Hmph.

272
00:22:25,180 --> 00:22:27,880
Keep doing that,
and you'll pull something.

273
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,080
You heading straight home?

274
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:57,360
Yeah.

275
00:22:57,520 --> 00:23:00,040
My mom just messaged me
to help Dad with something.

276
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,480
Okay. I'm heading home.

277
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:04,160
Let's go.

278
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,120
Hey, Save.

279
00:23:19,630 --> 00:23:20,630
Yeah?

280
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:26,400
If I tell you something,
can you promise you won't hate me?

281
00:23:27,470 --> 00:23:28,560
What is it? Just say it.

282
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,960
Well, I...

283
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,630
- I like...
- I'm waiting out front.

284
00:23:37,460 --> 00:23:38,860
Who were you just talking to?

285
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:41,610
It's Jang, asking me to go to Siam.

286
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:44,280
What about...
going home to help your dad?

287
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:46,860
Oh, that can wait.
Scoping out girls comes first.

288
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:49,640
So...you were saying?

289
00:23:51,140 --> 00:23:52,600
Nothing. Forget it.

290
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:54,520
Hey.

291
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,160
What is it? Tell me.

292
00:23:59,850 --> 00:24:00,850
It's just...

293
00:24:02,180 --> 00:24:03,840
I was going to say I...

294
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:07,800
like...

295
00:24:07,830 --> 00:24:09,000
Hey, Save.

296
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:11,700
Ow.

297
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:12,960
Hey, you okay?

298
00:24:13,340 --> 00:24:14,360
Ow, that hurt.

299
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:16,560
That's nothing. You're so dramatic.

300
00:24:19,510 --> 00:24:21,080
Guy, you coming with us or not?

301
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:22,360
- You in?
- Yeah, I'm in.

302
00:24:22,870 --> 00:24:26,550
Well, it's a mess, really.
I still don't know what to do.

303
00:24:28,730 --> 00:24:31,360
Thank you, honestly.
Thank you so much.

304
00:24:32,110 --> 00:24:33,640
I really appreciate it.

305
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:37,400
I won't forget this.
I really mean it.

306
00:24:52,950 --> 00:24:53,950
Hey.

307
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,800
Mom, where's the clock?

308
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:01,920
The one you always carry around.
Where is it?

309
00:25:11,140 --> 00:25:12,140
Where did you put it?

310
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:18,680
It's gone. Where did you leave it?

311
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:20,600
What are you looking for?

312
00:25:20,670 --> 00:25:23,480
The clock that was always up there.

313
00:25:23,940 --> 00:25:25,880
Oh, I haven't seen it at all.

314
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:28,040
No idea where Mom left it.

315
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:31,280
That clock isn't any regular one.

316
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:36,320
The former Army Commander gave it
to me as a wedding gift.

317
00:25:38,330 --> 00:25:40,200
Who were you on the phone with
just now?

318
00:25:40,530 --> 00:25:41,840
Me, on the phone?

319
00:25:42,110 --> 00:25:44,760
Yeah, you. I saw you on the phone.

320
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:46,680
Oh...

321
00:25:47,290 --> 00:25:49,200
Um, I was talking to...

322
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,200
- A friend.
- A friend?

323
00:25:52,510 --> 00:25:54,550
An old friend.
Hadn't spoken to in a while.

324
00:25:54,590 --> 00:25:56,790
Mm-hmm. So it took you
a while to answer me?

325
00:25:57,350 --> 00:25:58,220
Hehe.

326
00:25:58,240 --> 00:26:00,440
My, so forgetful at your age.

327
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:04,920
You'll be like my mom soon, huh?

328
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:08,880
And if you find that clock,
put it back where it belongs.

329
00:26:09,410 --> 00:26:10,600
Yes, Father.

330
00:26:10,620 --> 00:26:11,620
Right.

331
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:14,600
Mom, this can't keep happening.

332
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:17,200
Things keep going missing.

333
00:26:18,120 --> 00:26:19,480
I can't keep up with this.

334
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:25,680
Let's kick some ball.

335
00:26:31,830 --> 00:26:33,000
We're here already.

336
00:26:35,080 --> 00:26:39,080
Alright, engine's off.
Everyone can get out now.

337
00:26:39,910 --> 00:26:42,260
- Thank you.
- Yes, yes. Don't run. You'll fall.

338
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:44,880
- Thank you.
- Go on, kids. Watch yourself.

339
00:26:44,880 --> 00:26:46,240
- Easy, easy.
- Thank you.

340
00:26:46,270 --> 00:26:48,480
Oh, oh. Careful. Here.

341
00:26:48,740 --> 00:26:51,680
Slow down
or you'll trip over yourself.

342
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:54,800
Good girl.
Go wash up and do your homework.

343
00:26:54,830 --> 00:26:55,880
Alright, that's everyone.

344
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:56,880
Ugh.

345
00:26:57,590 --> 00:26:59,160
Pipe, you...

346
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:07,000
Hey, hey. Guys.

347
00:27:26,330 --> 00:27:27,440
I'm Snow.

348
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:28,520
I'm Mabel.

349
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:31,880
I'm Yoyo. What's your name?

350
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:33,880
My name is Jingjai.

351
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:39,560
Jingjai, Auntie Oui asked us
to look after you.

352
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:41,680
Come on, we'll give you
the home tour.

353
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:44,000
She already did.

354
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,920
But there are rules
you need to know.

355
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:51,480
I'm sure she didn't tell you.

356
00:27:55,320 --> 00:28:01,000
Bathroom rules.
Two minutes per person. That's it.

357
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:02,720
What? Only two minutes?

358
00:28:02,850 --> 00:28:03,850
Yes.

359
00:28:03,900 --> 00:28:10,000
If you go over, you're scrubbing
smelly toilets for a week.

360
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:13,240
It's not personal.
It just wastes water.

361
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:16,280
Right. Two minutes, no more.

362
00:28:20,370 --> 00:28:21,790
This is the dining area.

363
00:28:21,820 --> 00:28:25,100
We all come together
for every meal, every day.

364
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:26,840
Mealtime rules.

365
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:29,440
Finish everything on your plate.
Not a single grain left.

366
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:30,800
No food waste.

367
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:32,920
Trying to sneak it out?

368
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:35,170
You get no meal for a week.

369
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:37,440
That could starve someone to death.

370
00:28:38,990 --> 00:28:41,750
We all have to be frugal.
No throwing food away.

371
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:44,960
Every plate, every dish.

372
00:28:44,980 --> 00:28:48,060
Nothing goes to waste.
Food is precious.

373
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:51,600
And this is the computer room.

374
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:54,080
For homework and studying.

375
00:28:54,270 --> 00:28:58,080
If you want to use a computer,
sign in right there.

376
00:29:00,590 --> 00:29:02,600
But no more than thirty minutes.

377
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:07,200
If you go over,
no social media for you. Forever.

378
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,720
Don't linger.
It runs up the electric bill.

379
00:29:19,640 --> 00:29:21,640
Last stop: the bedroom.

380
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:24,320
Everyone lights out at nine.

381
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,760
If anyone refuses to sleep...

382
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,020
- The ghost will get you.
- The ghost will get you.

383
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:42,920
Hey, the power's out.

384
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:46,040
Get a flashlight.
I'll check on the kids.

385
00:29:46,250 --> 00:29:47,360
Hm...

386
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:51,960
The electric authority
said nothing about a blackout.

387
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:54,240
Oh, now I remember.

388
00:29:54,770 --> 00:29:56,720
- Remember what?
- I forgot to pay the bill.

389
00:29:56,750 --> 00:30:00,150
Sorn, it's important. How could you?

390
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:03,920
Well, Mart borrowed it that day to
get school uniforms for the kids.

391
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:06,720
She hasn't paid me back,
so it slipped my mind.

392
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:10,520
Don't blame me.
I just need more time.

393
00:30:10,580 --> 00:30:13,800
And you never reminded me.
I figured paid it after all.

394
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:15,760
Why did you assume?

395
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:20,200
I've got a lot to do:
deliveries, errands, on and on.

396
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:23,640
Of course, things slip my mind.
The borrower should follow up.

397
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:25,840
Ow, I'm busy too.

398
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:28,360
My head's spinning all the time.

399
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:30,800
Alright, alright. That's enough.

400
00:30:31,290 --> 00:30:32,680
Go pay it tomorrow.

401
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:35,440
Flashlight.
I'm gonna check on the kids.

402
00:30:36,630 --> 00:30:37,630
Oh.

403
00:30:38,490 --> 00:30:39,490
Yeah?

404
00:30:40,990 --> 00:30:42,720
Uh. What's going on?

405
00:30:42,860 --> 00:30:45,120
Dead batteries.
Haven't used it in ages.

406
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:48,360
What actually works in this house?

407
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:53,320
Happy birthday to you.

408
00:30:53,350 --> 00:30:54,400
Whose birthday is it?

409
00:30:54,430 --> 00:30:57,600
Haha. Don't mess around.
The power's out.

410
00:30:58,140 --> 00:31:00,160
Your dad forgot to pay the bill.

411
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:02,000
Your mom borrowed the money.

412
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:05,000
Alright, enough. It's fine.

413
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:07,840
Save, go check on the kids.

414
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:08,960
Yes.

415
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:10,920
Oh, and fetch Auntie Oui for me.

416
00:31:11,190 --> 00:31:12,190
Got it.

417
00:31:14,290 --> 00:31:17,520
And... where's the cake
and candles, Grandpa?

418
00:31:18,010 --> 00:31:18,720
Hmm?

419
00:31:18,850 --> 00:31:20,120
Cake and candles?

420
00:31:21,260 --> 00:31:24,340
Go now, or I'll push you there
with my foot.

421
00:31:24,360 --> 00:31:25,400
Oh, I'd better hurry.

422
00:31:25,870 --> 00:31:27,840
- Hurry with my foot?
- I'm going, I'm going.

423
00:31:40,030 --> 00:31:41,340
- Auntie Oui.
- Yes.

424
00:31:41,370 --> 00:31:42,370
Mom needs you.

425
00:31:42,390 --> 00:31:45,550
Oh, alright.
You keep an eye on the kids.

426
00:31:46,020 --> 00:31:47,240
Just watch them. That's it?

427
00:31:47,350 --> 00:31:49,000
Whatever you say, Save.

428
00:31:51,280 --> 00:31:52,280
This way.

429
00:31:58,910 --> 00:32:01,080
Phi (honorific) Save, I'm scared.

430
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:04,560
Why? You sleep with the lights off
every night.

431
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:07,110
Hmm?

432
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:11,560
But it's a blackout.
Is the house ghost messing with us?

433
00:32:12,280 --> 00:32:15,240
You mean Tiad?
He should've reincarnated ages ago.

434
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:16,880
Look...

435
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:19,000
Hey, Snow.

436
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:23,020
Hmm? You made up
a scary tale again?

437
00:32:23,190 --> 00:32:27,080
I did not. I did see him
in a photo smiling.

438
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:28,680
You were paranoid.

439
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,520
- I wasn't.
- Hey, guys.

440
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:33,780
How about something fun?

441
00:32:33,810 --> 00:32:35,810
Good idea, good idea.

442
00:32:35,860 --> 00:32:38,760
Quick. Gather round. Come close.

443
00:33:16,240 --> 00:33:18,360
And the final transformation.

444
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,360
A werewolf.

445
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:31,040
Wrruff!

446
00:33:39,850 --> 00:33:41,880
Save, come here a second.

447
00:33:41,900 --> 00:33:42,900
Coming.

448
00:33:43,210 --> 00:33:44,680
Snow, my phone please.

449
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:47,800
- I'll be right back, yeah?
- Phi Save, keep dancing.

450
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:50,040
Hey, I'll be back.
You guys stay put.

451
00:33:50,080 --> 00:33:52,200
Okay?. Be right back.

452
00:33:52,230 --> 00:33:53,520
- Phi Save...
- I'll come back.

453
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:55,720
Why? It's scary.

454
00:33:55,890 --> 00:33:57,600
That was terrifying.

455
00:33:57,630 --> 00:34:00,760
Mom always breaks up the fun.

456
00:34:01,250 --> 00:34:03,260
- Did you hurt bad?
- Ow.

457
00:34:03,260 --> 00:34:04,600
Reached up and my back went out.

458
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:05,760
Oh, no.

459
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:07,480
Yeah, Mom?

460
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:10,480
Your dad just threw out his back
reaching up there.

461
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,800
There. Get that box from up top.

462
00:34:12,920 --> 00:34:13,920
What do you need, Mom?

463
00:34:14,290 --> 00:34:16,280
A lantern for the kids.

464
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:19,240
Don't want to use candles.
Something might catch fire.

465
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:21,440
We should use electric lanterns.

466
00:34:21,720 --> 00:34:24,160
Nobody uses oil lanterns anymore.

467
00:34:24,630 --> 00:34:28,280
Right there is a brain.
Wonder where he gets that from.

468
00:34:29,150 --> 00:34:30,560
- Come on.
- Where?

469
00:34:31,060 --> 00:34:32,340
- There.
- Here?

470
00:34:32,370 --> 00:34:34,160
- Careful, it's high.
- Easy, easy.

471
00:34:34,160 --> 00:34:35,840
- Watch out.
- Dad, a little push.

472
00:34:37,230 --> 00:34:39,650
- Push him.
- Ow, hold on. Ugh.

473
00:34:39,670 --> 00:34:43,850
Support him. Easy now.
Watch that stuff on top.

474
00:34:45,660 --> 00:34:48,570
He's taking too long.
It's been forever.

475
00:34:49,720 --> 00:34:51,520
Mom and Dad definitely
put him to work.

476
00:34:52,030 --> 00:34:53,030
Mm.

477
00:35:03,180 --> 00:35:04,560
Hey, Pipe.

478
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:05,880
Shh.

479
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:10,760
Awoo.

480
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:15,720
- Awoo.
- Awoo.

481
00:35:15,900 --> 00:35:16,950
Look.

482
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:19,760
Awoo.

483
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,080
Not even close.

484
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:25,840
Well, you think you can do better?

485
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:34,400
Awoo...woo.

486
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:37,400
- Awoo...
- Awoo...

487
00:35:39,350 --> 00:35:42,120
Werewolf or mangy mutt.

488
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:47,280
- Mangy mutt.
- Mangy mutt.

489
00:35:48,050 --> 00:35:49,050
Hey.

490
00:36:04,230 --> 00:36:04,800
Ow.

491
00:36:04,830 --> 00:36:06,000
- Hey.
- Hey.

492
00:36:11,510 --> 00:36:13,880
Pipe, look what you did.

493
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:15,640
You knocked me first.

494
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:17,160
You pushed me first.

495
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:19,120
Because you shoved me.

496
00:36:19,120 --> 00:36:20,080
I did not.

497
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:21,840
Let's ask them.
They saw the whole thing.

498
00:36:28,970 --> 00:36:31,000
Fire. Fire.

499
00:36:33,740 --> 00:36:35,320
Hey. Fire.

500
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:39,500
- Hey.
- Hey, fire.

501
00:36:41,070 --> 00:36:42,160
Fire.

502
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:43,720
- What?
- What?

503
00:36:44,260 --> 00:36:46,360
- Hey.
- Go look.

504
00:36:50,820 --> 00:36:52,260
Everyone, get down.

505
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:59,400
Everyone, crawl to the door.

506
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,640
Dad, spray it. Spray it.

507
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:05,080
What's wrong, Dad?

508
00:37:05,230 --> 00:37:06,680
I don't know. Something's wrong.

509
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:08,320
Is it expired? Come on.

510
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:09,320
We're done for.

511
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:12,380
Ow. Everyone, follow me.

512
00:37:13,040 --> 00:37:14,240
Snow, why are you crawling?

513
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:17,040
To get under the smoke.
Everyone get down.

514
00:37:17,980 --> 00:37:19,360
There's hardly any smoke.

515
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:21,960
- Get up. Get out now.
- Get up.

516
00:37:21,960 --> 00:37:24,440
Out, out, out. Quick.

517
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:26,040
Children, this way.

518
00:37:26,060 --> 00:37:27,440
Go on, hurry along.

519
00:37:27,460 --> 00:37:29,060
Be careful.

520
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,290
- You got it?
- Whoa.

521
00:37:30,770 --> 00:37:31,800
Hey.

522
00:37:35,160 --> 00:37:36,600
Sorn, why aren't you spraying it?

523
00:37:36,740 --> 00:37:37,960
It won't come out.

524
00:37:38,820 --> 00:37:39,820
Whoa.

525
00:37:40,350 --> 00:37:41,600
Hack. Hack.

526
00:37:42,010 --> 00:37:43,010
Oh no.

527
00:37:47,450 --> 00:37:48,760
Ah, let's go.

528
00:37:50,630 --> 00:37:51,630
Hurry, hurry.

529
00:37:59,810 --> 00:38:00,600
Mom.
- Hey.
- What?

530
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:02,640
Good grief.

531
00:38:03,140 --> 00:38:04,680
Aw.

532
00:38:05,810 --> 00:38:07,160
Great-grandma,
how did you get here?

533
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:09,240
Her timing couldn't be worse.

534
00:38:11,160 --> 00:38:13,320
Dad, don't. I'll handle it.

535
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:14,840
Take her outside.

536
00:38:14,870 --> 00:38:15,870
Quickly.

537
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:17,000
Save, go get more buckets.

538
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,120
- Hurry. Give me that.
- Okay.

539
00:38:19,460 --> 00:38:20,480
- Here.
- Yes.

540
00:38:21,580 --> 00:38:22,960
- Water.
- Get Grandma out, Dad.

541
00:38:24,290 --> 00:38:25,650
Mom, let's go.

542
00:38:27,770 --> 00:38:30,180
- Please calm down.
- Ugh.

543
00:38:30,200 --> 00:38:31,480
Mom, stop fighting.

544
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:37,840
- Get out now.
- Hurry.

545
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:47,280
Is our house going to be okay?

546
00:38:47,540 --> 00:38:49,260
The whole place is gonna burn.

547
00:38:49,380 --> 00:38:52,400
And it'll spread to the neighbors.

548
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:56,280
Stink breath.
That's not gonna happen.

549
00:38:56,800 --> 00:39:00,120
It is burning.
All because of you, Pipe.

550
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:04,840
Yeah, you started it. Put it out.

551
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:06,880
Enough.
Everyone, follow me.

552
00:39:08,300 --> 00:39:09,300
Ow.

553
00:39:11,120 --> 00:39:12,360
How could it be broken?

554
00:39:12,390 --> 00:39:17,040
I still haven't found a husband.
I'm not ready to die.

555
00:39:17,330 --> 00:39:19,680
Water's here.
Mom, water.

556
00:39:19,700 --> 00:39:20,370
Water's here.

557
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:21,400
Here, here.

558
00:39:21,970 --> 00:39:23,840
Water's here.

559
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:25,960
Save, get more water.

560
00:39:25,990 --> 00:39:26,990
Okay.

561
00:39:27,010 --> 00:39:29,680
- We're here to help.
- Help is here.

562
00:39:53,920 --> 00:40:01,540
- Yeah...
- Yeah...

563
00:40:01,540 --> 00:40:03,160
We did it.

564
00:40:03,290 --> 00:40:05,240
We don't have to
sleep on the street after all.

565
00:40:05,690 --> 00:40:06,690
Oh.

566
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:08,640
Why did you say that, Mabel?

567
00:40:09,420 --> 00:40:13,320
Because without this house,
we'd have nowhere to go.

568
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:23,880
Huh.

569
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:28,340
Save's helping Auntie Oui
clean up now.

570
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:30,750
Tonight the kids should
be able to sleep inside.

571
00:40:30,770 --> 00:40:31,770
Mm.

572
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:35,960
Phi Sorn, pay the electric bill
right now.

573
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:39,520
I looked it up for our area.

574
00:40:39,520 --> 00:40:42,440
If we pay now,
they can still come out tonight.

575
00:40:42,470 --> 00:40:44,040
We'll have power back right away.

576
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:45,440
- Really?
- Mm.

577
00:40:46,220 --> 00:40:49,870
And we should get new bedding
and a new fire extinguisher.

578
00:40:50,130 --> 00:40:52,360
Alright. I'll pull money
from the bank.

579
00:40:53,040 --> 00:40:56,560
I'm afraid it's not enough
for the power bill.

580
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:59,080
Then I'll find a way.

581
00:40:59,670 --> 00:41:03,230
Dad, I know you love this place.

582
00:41:03,560 --> 00:41:04,960
I do too.

583
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:08,080
But we're getting
stretched too thin.

584
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:10,080
I'm working on it.

585
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,440
Father.

586
00:41:16,020 --> 00:41:17,440
The clock on the shelf.

587
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:20,120
Grandma didn't take it anywhere.

588
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:22,120
I did.

589
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:26,610
I've been quietly pawning off
old things from the house.

590
00:41:26,970 --> 00:41:28,230
Quite a few pieces by now.

591
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:30,790
What? No wonder.

592
00:41:31,370 --> 00:41:33,880
The place has been looking emptier.

593
00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:37,550
Mart, why didn't you
talk to us first?

594
00:41:38,070 --> 00:41:40,520
Well, if I'd told you that,

595
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:41,990
would you have let me?

596
00:41:42,010 --> 00:41:44,440
There might have been another way.

597
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:46,640
There wasn't another way.

598
00:41:47,510 --> 00:41:49,660
Otherwise, we wouldn't be
stressed out like this.

599
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:56,920
I'm sorry, Father.
But I really had no choice.

600
00:41:59,150 --> 00:42:02,000
Dad, don't be angry with Mart.

601
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:04,800
I'll find the money
to get everything out of pawn.

602
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:06,760
No need.

603
00:42:07,310 --> 00:42:10,000
I'm nearly done with
the second volume of my novel.

604
00:42:11,200 --> 00:42:14,920
Once it sells, we'll have cash
to work with again.

605
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:18,080
But Dad...

606
00:42:18,100 --> 00:42:19,100
That's final.

607
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:22,360
Remember to pay that electric bill.

608
00:42:23,010 --> 00:42:25,090
The kids need their lights back on.

609
00:42:28,340 --> 00:42:29,340
Yes.

610
00:42:50,140 --> 00:42:51,240
Hmm.

611
00:43:29,140 --> 00:43:30,140
Hmm.

612
00:43:48,230 --> 00:43:51,170
"The End."

613
00:43:58,270 --> 00:43:59,270
Whew.

614
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:05,560
Save, give me a hand.

615
00:44:06,690 --> 00:44:07,690
Yeah, Dad?

616
00:44:07,720 --> 00:44:09,880
Take Grandpa to the publisher.

617
00:44:10,280 --> 00:44:11,640
What? Right now?

618
00:44:11,840 --> 00:44:12,840
Of course.

619
00:44:15,340 --> 00:44:16,320
What?
Gas money.

620
00:44:22,200 --> 00:44:23,200
Hmm.

621
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:25,840
Hmm...

622
00:44:27,010 --> 00:44:28,010
Hmm.

623
00:44:28,350 --> 00:44:29,350
Uh-mmm.

624
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:30,400
Huh?

625
00:44:32,530 --> 00:44:34,420
Hmm. That's final.

626
00:44:35,150 --> 00:44:37,880
Dad, this is a car, not a motorbike.

627
00:44:37,880 --> 00:44:41,000
Well, just drive it easy then.

628
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:42,520
Easy how?

629
00:44:42,790 --> 00:44:44,090
Look it up online.

630
00:44:44,510 --> 00:44:47,030
Isn't that what you always say?

631
00:44:50,220 --> 00:44:51,220
Huh.

632
00:44:55,140 --> 00:44:56,500
How to save on gas.

633
00:44:57,600 --> 00:44:58,640
Sure thing.

634
00:44:58,790 --> 00:45:02,970
Here are the simple ways.
Start by driving smoothly.

635
00:45:02,970 --> 00:45:04,400
Avoid hitting the gas too hard.

636
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:08,000
On top of that, keeping up with
regular maintenance,

637
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:12,040
like proper tire pressure
and regular air filter changes

638
00:45:12,490 --> 00:45:14,280
can really save some gas.

639
00:45:15,720 --> 00:45:17,520
Oy...how much is that gonna save?

640
00:45:23,510 --> 00:45:24,550
Ahem.

641
00:45:26,240 --> 00:45:28,220
Well. Do you have enough cash?

642
00:45:28,660 --> 00:45:31,760
Yes, sir. Wait by the car.
I'll grab the keys first.

643
00:45:31,790 --> 00:45:32,790
Sure.

644
00:45:54,460 --> 00:45:55,460
Hmm.

645
00:45:55,810 --> 00:45:59,400
Scoot in a bit
or the sun will dry you out.

646
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:01,640
I'll get going now.

647
00:46:11,070 --> 00:46:12,110
Hmm...

648
00:46:14,820 --> 00:46:17,000
Heh...fun, wasn't it?

649
00:46:18,200 --> 00:46:19,160
Well...

650
00:46:19,160 --> 00:46:23,480
See? I still got it.
And I hadn't written in ages.

651
00:46:23,760 --> 00:46:25,520
The craft never left me.

652
00:46:25,520 --> 00:46:26,560
Haha.

653
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:30,440
Being a writer is in my blood.

654
00:46:30,970 --> 00:46:33,070
Cut me open,

655
00:46:33,570 --> 00:46:35,680
I bleed words.
Your father knew that.

656
00:46:37,410 --> 00:46:38,600
- Sir.
- Yes?

657
00:46:38,930 --> 00:46:39,960
Sorry to say this.

658
00:46:40,310 --> 00:46:42,640
But... Saming the Slayer, Volume 1,

659
00:46:42,670 --> 00:46:45,800
that my father published in '97,
out of kindness,

660
00:46:46,120 --> 00:46:47,140
was...

661
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:50,000
uhm...

662
00:46:50,330 --> 00:46:53,450
Seeing you today
actually reminded me

663
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:55,150
of unsold stock in the warehouse.

664
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:57,880
I had someone bring it over
to donate it.

665
00:46:58,920 --> 00:47:00,710
Oh, doing some good then.

666
00:47:01,200 --> 00:47:04,080
Wonderful. I rejoice in your merit.

667
00:47:04,080 --> 00:47:05,490
Yeah. And here...

668
00:47:06,050 --> 00:47:08,800
Saming the Slayer from '97.

669
00:47:10,140 --> 00:47:11,680
Why? I don't see anything strange.

670
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:14,440
Any novel, no matter who writes it,

671
00:47:14,460 --> 00:47:18,820
has a few copies come back unsold.
Perfectly normal.

672
00:47:18,820 --> 00:47:19,820
Hehe.

673
00:47:20,320 --> 00:47:21,320
Yes.

674
00:47:23,090 --> 00:47:24,390
Um...sir.

675
00:47:27,540 --> 00:47:30,710
Here's the thing. All of this.

676
00:47:31,360 --> 00:47:34,240
These are all yours.

677
00:47:34,480 --> 00:47:35,480
What?

678
00:47:38,990 --> 00:47:39,990
That can't be right.

679
00:47:40,250 --> 00:47:41,250
It is, sir.

680
00:47:41,310 --> 00:47:43,240
It...can't be.

681
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:46,030
"Palang Publishing"

682
00:47:46,420 --> 00:47:47,420
"Guy: Whatchu up to?"

683
00:47:48,880 --> 00:47:50,240
"Save: An errand with Grandpa."

684
00:47:50,760 --> 00:47:51,880
"Guy: Where to after?"

685
00:47:52,830 --> 00:47:54,640
"Save: Not sure. Probably home."

686
00:47:57,720 --> 00:47:59,960
"Guy: I want to see you. Can we?"

687
00:48:09,840 --> 00:48:10,920
I understand that...

688
00:48:12,240 --> 00:48:14,760
Volume 1 may not have
hit its sales target.

689
00:48:14,760 --> 00:48:17,230
But there are people out there
asking for Volume 2.

690
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:19,360
Who, exactly?

691
00:48:19,680 --> 00:48:20,680
Um...

692
00:48:22,210 --> 00:48:23,360
Pull up a website for me.

693
00:48:24,040 --> 00:48:27,280
Someone mentioned
a site about novels.

694
00:48:29,250 --> 00:48:30,520
There. Right there.

695
00:48:31,360 --> 00:48:33,200
Search for my pen name,
Harn Chanprai.

696
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:36,840
Okay.

697
00:48:40,140 --> 00:48:41,140
See?

698
00:48:42,100 --> 00:48:45,280
Missing earth's scent, jungle hush,
the grip of danger in Harn's novels.

699
00:48:45,280 --> 00:48:48,560
Anyone else waiting
for Saming the Slayer Volume 2?

700
00:48:49,080 --> 00:48:53,200
Next comment. Been waiting
nearly 30 years to read it.

701
00:48:53,570 --> 00:48:56,680
No one rivals Harn Chanprai.

702
00:48:56,680 --> 00:48:59,120
I want to go back into that forest
one more time.

703
00:48:59,120 --> 00:49:01,760
I need to know if
that Saming (were-tiger)

704
00:49:03,050 --> 00:49:04,120
is truly finished.

705
00:49:07,680 --> 00:49:08,680
You see?

706
00:49:09,520 --> 00:49:11,510
I didn't want
to let these fans down.

707
00:49:11,510 --> 00:49:15,520
So I pushed myself
to finish Volume 2.

708
00:49:15,890 --> 00:49:17,880
But sir, there are only 12 comments.

709
00:49:21,260 --> 00:49:23,680
Sir, I genuinely cannot
publish this for you.

710
00:49:25,000 --> 00:49:26,480
I'm being honest with you.

711
00:49:26,480 --> 00:49:28,880
My publishing house is
barely staying afloat.

712
00:49:33,200 --> 00:49:36,540
Phuri, I need this to sell.

713
00:49:39,990 --> 00:49:41,030
I need the money.

714
00:49:43,670 --> 00:49:47,080
I'm afraid...you'll need to
write something the market wants.

715
00:49:47,640 --> 00:49:49,640
It might be worth looking into

716
00:49:49,660 --> 00:49:51,810
what people are reading these days.

717
00:49:55,400 --> 00:49:56,860
"Save: You okay?"

718
00:50:03,480 --> 00:50:05,800
"Guy: Something important
to talk to you today."

719
00:50:07,040 --> 00:50:08,120
"Save: Just say it then."

720
00:50:19,040 --> 00:50:22,040
Save, take me to a bookstore.

721
00:50:24,730 --> 00:50:26,010
Hmm. Which one?

722
00:50:26,280 --> 00:50:29,040
Whichever one people go to
these days.

723
00:50:30,470 --> 00:50:31,470
All right.

724
00:50:33,160 --> 00:50:35,720
No need. I can walk myself.

725
00:50:36,550 --> 00:50:38,160
Hmph. Show-off, huh?

726
00:50:38,550 --> 00:50:40,600
You fall and no one's gonna feel
sorry for you.

727
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:46,840
"Save: Going to a bookstore at Siam.
Just say what you gotta say."

728
00:50:53,250 --> 00:50:56,840
"Guy: I'm at Siam too.
Come find me. Same spot."

729
00:50:57,120 --> 00:50:58,120
What's with him?

730
00:51:00,480 --> 00:51:01,480
Grandpa...

731
00:51:03,240 --> 00:51:05,040
Stay inside the store.
Don't go anywhere.

732
00:51:05,480 --> 00:51:07,280
I go see a friend. Be right back.

733
00:51:07,770 --> 00:51:08,770
Mm-hmm.

734
00:51:38,880 --> 00:51:40,080
I'm over here.

735
00:51:41,920 --> 00:51:45,320
Guy, what's on your mind?
Been holding back since yesterday.

736
00:51:46,440 --> 00:51:49,940
We're friends.
You can tell me anything.

737
00:51:51,230 --> 00:51:54,000
My Close Friends account,
you asked who's in it.

738
00:51:55,060 --> 00:51:56,480
It's only you.

739
00:51:57,600 --> 00:52:00,240
So what? Just add other people.

740
00:52:01,000 --> 00:52:03,440
No. I only want you in it.

741
00:52:07,500 --> 00:52:08,920
So cute.

742
00:52:10,270 --> 00:52:11,560
- Hey, let me see.
- Here.

743
00:52:16,460 --> 00:52:19,410
I mean I only want you
to see what I post.

744
00:52:21,500 --> 00:52:22,500
Why?

745
00:52:23,200 --> 00:52:24,320
You still don't get it?

746
00:52:24,880 --> 00:52:27,200
What is it? Just say it.

747
00:52:27,800 --> 00:52:30,040
I've been sitting on this
for a long time.

748
00:52:30,680 --> 00:52:32,560
After I say this, I don't know

749
00:52:32,840 --> 00:52:34,160
if anything will be the same.

750
00:52:35,620 --> 00:52:36,720
But...

751
00:52:59,160 --> 00:53:01,160
Save, I like you.

752
00:53:03,900 --> 00:53:05,620
"Until the Time is Right"

753
00:53:05,640 --> 00:53:06,640
Hey.

754
00:53:22,130 --> 00:53:25,240
If we can't hold on,
better sell the orphanage.

755
00:53:25,920 --> 00:53:29,000
I won't. I'm going to write
a Boys' Love novel.

756
00:53:29,480 --> 00:53:31,000
Make enough to clear the debt.

757
00:53:31,240 --> 00:53:33,920
Grandpa, you don't have to hide it.
I already know.

758
00:53:34,280 --> 00:53:38,020
You think your BL novel
will save this house?

759
00:53:38,260 --> 00:53:39,180
Of course.

760
00:53:39,200 --> 00:53:40,900
Guy, how about we give this a try?

761
00:53:42,150 --> 00:53:47,960
The world keeps
turning every day.

762
00:53:47,960 --> 00:53:53,360
And we keep
turning in its play.

763
00:53:53,360 --> 00:53:56,620
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

764
00:53:56,810 --> 00:53:59,270
We just might see
the world within.

765
00:53:59,310 --> 00:54:03,280
Let's walk together,
day by day.

766
00:54:03,450 --> 00:54:08,320
Come take the step,
what do you say?

767
00:54:14,830 --> 00:54:18,600
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

768
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:22,560
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

769
00:54:22,560 --> 00:54:27,640
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

770
00:54:27,640 --> 00:54:29,920
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

771
00:54:29,920 --> 00:54:32,640
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

772
00:54:32,640 --> 00:54:37,520
And land where
our hearts both grow.

773
00:54:37,960 --> 00:54:43,800
The world keeps
turning every day.

774
00:54:43,800 --> 00:54:49,120
And we keep
turning in its play.

775
00:54:49,120 --> 00:54:52,240
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

776
00:54:52,520 --> 00:54:55,080
We just might see
the world within.

777
00:54:55,080 --> 00:54:59,200
Let's walk together,
day by day.

778
00:54:59,200 --> 00:55:04,240
Come take the step,
what do you say?
